{"title_page": "Chimanimani National Reserve", "text_new": "[[File:Mt Binga Mozambique.JPG|thumb|right|250px|The reserve includes [[Monte Binga]], the highest point in Mozambique]]\n'''Chimanimani National Reserve''' ([[Portuguese language|Portuguese]]: Reserva Nacional de Chimanimani) is a [[Protected areas of Mozambique|protected area]] in [[Manica Province]] of [[Mozambique]]. It is located in the [[Chimanimani Mountains]] on the border with [[Zimbabwe]], and together with Zimbabwe's [[Chimanimani National Park]] it forms the Chimanimani Transfrontier Park.<ref name=bri>{{cite book |last1=Briggs |first1=Philip |title=Mozambique |date=2014 | pages=221-222 |publisher=Bradt Travel Guides |isbn=1841624969}}</ref>\n\nThe reserve was proclaimed in 2003, and has an area of 634 km<sup>2</sup>. The reserve includes the Mozambican portion of the Chimanimani Mountains, including [[Monte Binga]] (2436 m), Mozambique's highest peak. The reserve has a larger buffer zone (1723 km2)<ref>Hudson, A., Milliken, W., Timberlake, J. et al. Natural Plant Resources for Sustainable Development: Insights from Community Use in the Chimanimani Trans-Frontier Conservation Area, Mozambique. Hum Ecol 48, 55\u201367 (2020). [https://doi.org/10.1007/s10745-020-00132-w]</ref>, which extends into lower-elevation areas to the south, east, and north, and includes the [[Moribane Forest Reserve|Moribane]], Mpunga, Maronga, and Zomba forest reserves. The forest Moribane, Mpunga, and Maronga reserves were established in 1953.<ref>Ghiurghi, Andrea & Dondeyne, S. & Bannerman, J.. (2010). Chimanimani national reserve: management plan. 10.13140/2.1.1734.6240.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscategory-inline|Chimanimani National Reserve}}\n\n{{coordinates|19|47|42|S|33|05|21|E|region:MZ_type:landmark|display=title|name=Chimanimani National Reserve}}\n\n[[Category:Eastern Zimbabwe montane forest-grassland mosaic]]\n[[Category:Geography of Manica Province]]\n[[Category:Geography of Manicaland Province]]\n[[Category:Protected areas established in 2003]]\n[[Category:Protected areas of Mozambique]]\n\n{{Mozambique-geo-stub}}\n{{Africa-protected-area-stub}}\n", "text_old": "[[File:Mt Binga Mozambique.JPG|thumb|right|250px|The reserve includes [[Monte Binga]], the highest point in Mozambique]]\n'''Chimanimani National Reserve''' ([[Portuguese language|Portuguese]]: Reserva Nacional de Chimanimani) is a [[Protected areas of Mozambique|protected area in [[Manica Province]] of [[Mozambique]]. It is located in the [[Chimanimani Mountains]] on the border with [[Zimbabwe]], and together with Zimbabwe's [[Chimanimani National Park]] it forms the Chimanimani Transfrontier Park.<ref name=bri>{{cite book |last1=Briggs |first1=Philip |title=Mozambique |date=2014 | pages=221-222 |publisher=Bradt Travel Guides |isbn=1841624969}}</ref>\n\nThe reserve was proclaimed in 2003, and has an area of 634 km<sup>2</sup>. The reserve includes the Mozambican portion of the Chimanimani Mountains, including [[Monte Binga]] (2436 m), Mozambique's highest peak. The reserve has a larger buffer zone (1723 km2)<ref>Hudson, A., Milliken, W., Timberlake, J. et al. Natural Plant Resources for Sustainable Development: Insights from Community Use in the Chimanimani Trans-Frontier Conservation Area, Mozambique. Hum Ecol 48, 55\u201367 (2020). [https://doi.org/10.1007/s10745-020-00132-w]</ref>, which extends into lower-elevation areas to the south, east, and north, and includes the [[Moribane Forest Reserve|Moribane]], Mpunga, Maronga, and Zomba forest reserves. The forest Moribane, Mpunga, and Maronga reserves were established in 1953.<ref>Ghiurghi, Andrea & Dondeyne, S. & Bannerman, J.. (2010). Chimanimani national reserve: management plan. 10.13140/2.1.1734.6240.</ref>\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{commonscategory-inline|Chimanimani National Reserve}}\n\n{{coordinates|19|47|42|S|33|05|21|E|region:MZ_type:landmark|display=title|name=Chimanimani National Reserve}}\n\n[[Category:Eastern Zimbabwe montane forest-grassland mosaic]]\n[[Category:Geography of Manica Province]]\n[[Category:Geography of Manicaland Province]]\n[[Category:Protected areas established in 2003]]\n[[Category:Protected areas of Mozambique]]\n\n{{Mozambique-geo-stub}}\n{{Africa-protected-area-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Tom Radulovich", "label": "safe", "comment": "fix link", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Chimanimani_National_Reserve"}
